{"questionListItems":[{"id":"cluhz8np4008j124ykqh617o9","title":"Can I refer a case to the CMC for mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008k124ytf6kzwri","body":"<div>If you are representative from an agency, you can refer a case to the CMC through one the following modes:<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span></div><div>                                                                1. By calling the Minlaw Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 during office hours </div><div>                                                                                               2. Submitting an online application that is available on CMC's website                                        </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np4008l124yghidxybn","title":"If I applied for voluntary mediation but received no reply, can I bring the case up to the Tribunal?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008m124yeozpkzw0","body":"To file a claim at the CDRT against your neighbour, you need to personally file online using your Singpass at Community Justice and Tribunals System (CJTS) at www.statecourts.gov.sg/CJTS. For more information on the CDRT process please visit the State Courts website at www.statecourts.gov.sg or contact them at 1800 587 8423.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np4008n124y0zz1juri","title":"Can I have a virtual mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008o124yxvy3q805","body":"Mediation conducted by the CMC will be held at the government gazetted location which is currently at 45 Maxwell Road, URA Centre East Wing, Level 7.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np4008p124ytn91wdqu","title":"Do I have to pay any fee for mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008q124yqaum3254","body":"The person who applies for mediation will have to pay a one-time administrative fee of S$5.00 on the day of mediation.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np4008r124ylqe886as","title":"Can I record the mediation session?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008s124ydmtua7x5","body":"No. As set out by the CMC Act, Cap 49A, mediation at the CMC is a confidential process. Parties are not allowed to record anything (video or audio) during a mediation session.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np4008t124ybgrhjrmy","title":"If the Respondent does not appear for mediation, what can I do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np4008u124y52hq7g7u","body":"<div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">As mediation at the CMC is a voluntary process, we will only be able to proceed when both parties agree and attend the scheduled mediation session. You may wish to consider other legal options. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span></div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np5008v124yg1omphgg","title":"How do I complain about a mediator at the Community Mediation Centre?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np5008w124yxk74fn51","body":"<div></div>Please provide your feedback through the SMS link that has been sent to your mobile phone after your mediation session. Alternatively, you can also provide your feedback via our Online Enquiry Form that can be found on  our website at https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/<div> </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np5008x124yp1zzafg9","title":"I have received a letter from CMC. I do not wish to mediate. What do I need to do?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np5008y124y066zb8ce","body":"Please call the Minlaw Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 during office hours and inform them whether you would like to decline the invitation. Alternatively, you can submit your response via the online form at https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/<a href=\"http://www.mlaw.gov.sg/eservices/enquiry/\" target=\"_blank\"></a>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np5008z124yrerbab15","title":"Can I lodge a complaint against my neighbours?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np50090124ynm8uvq8h","body":"<div>If you are facing one of the following problems and have tried talking to your nieghbour without success, you can apply for mediation at the CMC:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Types of neighbour disputes that are suitable for the CMC mediation include </div><div>1.  Activities that generate unacceptable smell </div><div>2. Activities that generate excessive smoke </div><div>3. Animal related complaints </div><div>4. Causing damage to property </div><div>5. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </div><div>6. Dripping of water from laundry or other sources </div><div>7. Littering </div><div>8. Misuse or obstruction of common property </div><div>9. Noise generated from activities done within a residence </div><div>10. Noise generated from activities outside a place of residence </div><div>11. Utterance of unacceptable words</div><div> </div><div> You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service</div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np50091124ykt8r9bi9","title":"What is the Community Dispute Resolution Tribunals (CDRT)?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np50092124yzeyonk8k","body":"The Community Disputes Resolution Tribunal (CDRT) was set up under the auspices of the State Courts to hear cases that come under the purview of the Community Disputes Resolution Act (CDRA). For more information, please contact the State Courts at 1800 587 8423 or visit their website at www.statecourts.gov.sg  for detailed and up to date information.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np50093124ypuxca5z5","title":"I have no money. Can I request for free mediation with my neighbours?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np50094124ynj4m05nr","body":"You can approach the grassroots leaders from the RC nearest to your residence to seek mediation assistance at no cost.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np50095124yywspfpfp","title":"What happens if there is a settlement at the mediation session?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np50096124ysjotvagp","body":"If parties come to an agreement, the terms of the agreement will be put in writing. Parties will sign the agreement if they are agreeable to be bound by the terms.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np50097124yqmzd6z0f","title":"Can mediation be held near my residence?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np50098124yla9kjw5w","body":"Mediation conducted by the CMC will be held at the government gazetted location which is currently at 45 Maxwell Road, URA Centre East Wing, Level 7.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np60099124ye0vf2tcz","title":"Do I need the Respondent's contact number to apply for mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np6009a124yktizp1z0","body":"In order for CMC to invite the Respondent for a mediation session, we would require the Respondent's postal address. We will then send an invitation to mediate to the Respondent.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np6009b124y631t60ey","title":"Can CMC accept cases involving neighbour disputes in private condonominium or landed property?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np6009c124ymacx10bi","body":"<div>You can use CMC's mediation service to mediate any social, relational or community issues with your neighbour, regardless of whether you are staying in a public housing or private housing.                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Types of neighbour disputes that are suitable for the CMC mediation include </div><div> </div><div> </div><div>1.  Activities that generate unacceptable smell </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                               2. Activities that generate excessive smoke </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                     3. Animal related complaints </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              4. Causing damage to property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           5. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                          6. Dripping of water from laundry or other sources </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                      7. Littering </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                8. Misuse or obstruction of common property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                9. Noise generated from activities done within a residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                      10. Noise generated from activities outside a place of residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                            11. Utterance of unacceptable words </div><div> </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                             You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service</div><div> </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}}],"webResult":null,"count":936,"agency":{"id":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","name":"Ministry of Law","code":"mlaw","homepageUrl":"https://www.mlaw.gov.sg","enquiryPageUrl":"https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/","scope":"GLOBAL","emailDomainWhitelist":[],"type":"SCRAPED","minimumDayResponseTime":3,"responseTimeRange":10,"logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png","searchHint":"Legal Aid, Public Trustee","description":null,"trendingTerms":[],"hasSubjectTriaging":false,"subjects":[]},"currentPage":7,"matchedTokens":null,"agencyTopics":[{"id":729,"qcount":189,"title":"Precious Stones and Precious Metals Dealers","agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"priority":0,"subtopics":[{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":730,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":53,"title":"Reporting Requirement - Semi-Annual Return"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":1454,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":38,"title":"Regulatory Regime - CTR Filing / CDD matters"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":735,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":36,"title":"Registration and Renewal"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":732,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":17,"title":"Regulatory Regime - Guidance"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":736,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":9,"title":"myPal - Screening Function"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x